{
  "_comment": "Scoped permissions for the headless cs-operator tick (claude -p '/cs-operator'). HARD RULE: not one allowed command can send mail to a customer. Drafting goes through the structurally-send-incapable verbs `draft-reply` (engine, allow_tools always empty) and `campaign queue-draft` (Gmail Drafts only, never SMTP). The send-capable surfaces — `cs chat` (can carry --allow send_email) and `cs campaign send-draft` (send mode) — are DENIED here; going autonomous-send later is a deliberate widening of THIS file, the real trust boundary. Still verify with a supervised headless run that it neither halts nor over-grants before installing the cron.",n  "permissions": {
